gr.forth.ics.swkm.model2.labels
Class PredefinedLabels

java.lang.Object
  gr.forth.ics.swkm.model2.labels.PredefinedLabels

public abstract class PredefinedLabels
extends Object

An entity that defines predefined labels for particular Resources. This may be used to customize the labels produced by a LabelManager so that specific nodes will have exactly the required labels, and not labels generated by the labeling algorithm.

Author:
Andreou Dimitris, email: jim.andreou (at) gmail (dot) com

public abstract Label predefinedLabelOf(Uri resourceURI)
Returns a predefined label of the specified resource, if there is one, or null otherwise.

Parameters:
resourceURI - the resource URI for which to return a fixed label, if the resource must have a fixed label
Returns:
the fixed Label instance that the resource must have, or null if the specified resource does not have any fixed label, but the LabelManager should create a label for it

merge

public PredefinedLabels merge(PredefinedLabels otherPredefinedLabels)
Creates a new PredefinedLabels by merging this instance with the specified one. In case where a predefined label is defined by both instances for the same URI, the latter is used, i.e. the predefined labels provided as a parameter override the labels of this instance.
